adqlParser.query
Class ADQLConstraint

java.lang.Object
  adqlParser.query.ADQLConstraint
All Implemented Interfaces:
ADQLObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
ADQLComparison, ADQLFunction, ADQLGroup
public abstract class ADQLConstraint
extends java.lang.Object
implements ADQLObject

Represents any kind of constraint.

To take in account the NOT keyword you just have to use the setNot(boolean) function.

A list of constraints is implemented by a linked list. Thus to add a constraint to a list you must use on the parent constraint the addConstraint(ADQLConstraint) (the concatenation operator is AND) or the addConstraint(ADQLConstraint,boolean) (the concatenation operator is specified by the 2nd parameter) functions.

Version:
06/2010
Author:
Grégory Mantelet (CDS)
